APPLICATION INTEGRATION (crates/scriptbots-app/src/main.rs:1-63)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Architecture Overview:
The main application now includes a bootstrap_world() function that initializes
a WorldState with DuckDB persistence, seeds 16 agents in a grid layout, runs
120 initial simulation steps, and logs the resulting summary. This provides
a working end-to-end integration example and primes the database with initial
telemetry data before the GPUI render loop starts.

Bootstrap Function (lines 20-52):

```rust
fn bootstrap_world() -> Result<()> {
    let mut config = ScriptBotsConfig::default();
    config.persistence_interval = 60;
    config.history_capacity = 600;

    let storage = Storage::open("scriptbots.db")?;
    let mut world = WorldState::with_persistence(config, Box::new(storage))?;

    seed_agents(&mut world);

    for _ in 0..120 {
        world.step();
    }

    if let Some(summary) = world.history().last() {
        info!(
            tick = summary.tick.0,
            agents = summary.agent_count,
            births = summary.births,
            deaths = summary.deaths,
            avg_energy = summary.average_energy,
            "Primed world and persisted initial summary",
        );
    } else {
        warn!("World bootstrap completed without persistence summaries");
    }

    Ok(())
}
```

Configuration tuning:
• persistence_interval: 60 ticks
  - At 60fps: Flush every 1 second (reasonable for real-time monitoring)
  - Database writes: ~60 writes/minute (low overhead)
• history_capacity: 600 entries
  - At 1Hz flush rate: 600 seconds = 10 minutes of history
  - Memory: 600 × 40 bytes = 24KB (negligible)

Storage initialization:
```rust
let storage = Storage::open("scriptbots.db")?;
```
• Creates or opens DuckDB database file
• Schema auto-created if not exists (tick_metrics table)
• File location: Current working directory
• Future: Make path configurable via CLI arg

World construction:
```rust
let mut world = WorldState::with_persistence(config, Box::new(storage))?;
```
• Uses with_persistence() constructor (not default new())
• Passes boxed Storage as trait object (Box<dyn WorldPersistence>)
• Result: Persistence enabled from construction

Warmup loop:
```rust
for _ in 0..120 {
    world.step();
}
```
• Runs 120 ticks = 2 seconds at 60fps
• Ensures at least 2 persistence flushes (60-tick interval)
• Primes database with initial data
• Allows agents to spread out and interact

Summary logging:
```rust
if let Some(summary) = world.history().last() {
    info!(tick = summary.tick.0, agents = summary.agent_count, ...);
}
```
• Retrieves most recent summary from history
• Uses structured logging (tracing crate)
• Fields: tick, agents, births, deaths, avg_energy
• Confirms bootstrap succeeded

Error handling:
• Result<()> return type
• ? operator propagates Storage and WorldState errors
• main() calls bootstrap_world()? (fails fast if error)
• Alternative: Could recover gracefully, disable persistence

Seed Function (lines 54-63):

```rust
fn seed_agents(world: &mut WorldState) {
    let mut agent = AgentData::default();
    let spacing = 120.0;
    for row in 0..4 {
        for col in 0..4 {
            agent.position.x = col as f32 * spacing + spacing * 0.5;
            agent.position.y = row as f32 * spacing + spacing * 0.5;
            agent.heading = 0.0;
            agent.spike_length = 10.0;
            world.spawn_agent(agent);
        }
    }
}
```

Grid layout:
• 4×4 grid = 16 agents
• Spacing: 120 units
• Offset: +spacing/2 (60 units from edge)
• Grid bounds: 60 to 420 (fits in 512×512 world)

Position calculation:
• X: col × 120 + 60 = [60, 180, 300, 420]
• Y: row × 120 + 60 = [60, 180, 300, 420]
• Result: Evenly distributed agents

Agent properties:
• position: Grid coordinates (as above)
• heading: 0.0 (facing right, +X axis)
• spike_length: 10.0 (moderate spike)
• Other fields: Default values (AgentData::default())
  - color: [0.0, 0.0, 0.0] (black)
  - velocity: 0.0 (stationary initially)
  - health: 1.0 (half max health)
  - age: 0 (newborn)
  - generation: 0 (founder generation)

Spawning:
```rust
world.spawn_agent(agent);
```
• Allocates AgentId via SlotMap
• Inserts data into SoA arena
• Creates default AgentRuntime
• Registers in spatial index
• No brain assigned (Unbound state)

Why no brains?
• Bootstrap focuses on infrastructure testing
• Brains will be assigned in render loop or via UI
• Agents without brains use zero outputs (no movement)
• Useful for testing persistence/sensing without behavior

Main Function Integration (lines 7-12):

```rust
fn main() -> Result<()> {
    init_tracing();
    bootstrap_world()?;
    info!("Starting ScriptBots simulation shell");
    run_demo();
    Ok(())
}
```

Execution order:
1. init_tracing(): Configure tracing subscriber
2. bootstrap_world(): Initialize world, seed agents, persist data
3. log info message
4. run_demo(): Start GPUI render loop
5. Return Ok(())

Error propagation:
• bootstrap_world()? fails fast if database error
• Prevents starting render loop with broken persistence
• User sees error immediately (not silent failure)

Tracing output example:
```
INFO scriptbots_app: Primed world and persisted initial summary tick=120 agents=16 births=0 deaths=0 avg_energy=1.0
INFO scriptbots_app: Starting ScriptBots simulation shell
```

Database state after bootstrap:
```sql
SELECT * FROM tick_metrics LIMIT 3;
